parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to remain loose or have excess slack, which can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract on its own
requires hand-feeding to retract
remains fully extended after being unbuckled
has excess slack while driving
twists and folds getting stuck within the guide rings
and may shred along the outer edges.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission synchronizer can cause the transmission to seize while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission seizes while driving
the vehicle jerks heavily
making it hard to control
the transmission leaks fluid
the transmission has a severe vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transfer case leak can cause the all-wheel-drive system to lock up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The transfer case leaks fluid
the transfer case output shaft is loose
causing a severe vibration
the all-wheel-drive system locks up
making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission and Transfer Case Oil Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leaks from the transmission and transfer case can cause the components to run dry, leading to damage and potential failure, which can result in loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The transmission and transfer case leak oil
the components run dry
causing damage and potential failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof glass can cause injuries, damage to the vehicle, and create a hazardous driving environment.
symptoms: The sunroof glass shatters without warning
often while the vehicle is parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning rear window wiper switch can cause the rear wiper to remain on constantly, leading to battery drain, water accumulation, and reduced visibility.
symptoms: The rear window wiper switch fails to disengage
leaving the rear wiper on constantly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accumulation of film on the inside windows can reduce visibility, creating a hazardous driving environment.
symptoms: Film builds up on the inside windows
causing visibility problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inoperative windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers fail to operate
reducing visibility during inclement weather.
